6:
Why are these people gathered
around? They sound very excited.
11:
Meh, I bet it's just an ad for a new
product or something. Count me out
if it's AltMeme.
15:
We should get a move on. I don't
feel like getting mobbed by bounty
hunters today.
18:
Tell me again why you've brought
me with you?
21:
Wellll, my ammo stash is running
low and they don't make ones for
my guns anywhere else, but I can't
just waltz in alone.
25:
That's where you come in. Your
handy-dandy senses are better
than any high-tech perimeter
scanner!
28:
So I'm a stand-in for a machine. I'm
not sure how to feel about that...
32:
Uh, excuse me? Are you by any
chance Bulleta?
35:
The one and only. What can I do for
you?
41:
I'm a HUUUUGE fan! Can I have your
autograph?!
48:
Wait. Didn't you say you have a
bounty on your head?
52:
That's what I thought.
Say, can someone tell me what's
going on? Not that I'm not flattered,
but this isn't the reception I was
expecting.
55:
You didn't see the ad? The one
saying you cracked open the dome?
You're a hero!
57:
With the shattering of the dome, one
troubleshooter became the heroine
of the sky, ridding the world of
corporate greed and saving the
noble princess!
58:
And now, for the first time, the true
story behind the hero will be
revealed on the big screen!
59:
With a star-studded cast and the
production value you've come to
know and love from Paradigm Break
Co., "The Bullet of Freedom" is sure to
pierce hearts everywhere!
63:
That slimy King John-sunuva... He
doesn't know when to stop!
66:
Come on, Light! I'll be damned if
they turn my life into a for-profit
farce!
70:
R-right. But how will you get a
meeting with him?
74:
By crashing straight through his
C-suite cruiser and blasting him out
of the dome! How else?!
85:
About time! The film production
team was going to start without you
95:
Why don't we take this somewhere
else? I've got a lot of questions and
you're going to give me answers.
101:
What will you have? I've got a bottle
of champagne, if you'd like a glass.
105:
I doubt the establishment would
take kindly to us bringing drinks in
from outside...
108:
Two unsynthesized milks, if you don't
mind.
113:
This is a celebratory event. Surely
you can choose something a little
less pedestrian.
*sigh* Fine. Make that three
unsynthesized milks.
118:
Now, to business.
I'm not some sort of idol or movie
star. I'm sure even you can see how
damaging this is to my brand as a
troubleshooter.
121:
Why would I want to tarnish your
brand? On the contrary, I'm giving
you a PR makeover!
125:
I even had the bounty on you lifted
and put the amount they were
offering into repairing the dome.
129:
Haha! You're a free woman now!
And it's all thanks to me!
131:
Somehow I doubt you did it purely
out of the goodness of your heart.
135:
Ahaha... Oh, there's no need for you
to be so guarded with me, Bulleta
Noche.
137:
You played your hand and cashed
out big-time. All I'm doing is giving
you your just reward.
142:
Is that really all there is to it? Where's
the profit in it for you?
144:
Let's just say that seeing people who
don't know the whole story stick their
necks into this whole mess touched
a nerve.
145:
And that's exactly why I'd like to cut
a deal with you.
149:
Won't you be the hero Qualia
Cityno, the worldneeds?
150:
Fame, fortune, and prestige would
be your oysters. I could make you a
star so bright and so high nothing
would bring you down.
153:
You would be a legend. And all you
have to do is say yes.
159:
I never once fought for fame or
fortune.
160:
Everything I did was for my
one-and-only partner; I don't want
to sully my gift to her with other
distractions.
162:
I'm grateful that you restored my
reputation. Truly, I am... But
friendship was and will always be
my main motivation.
166:
I see... That's a pity. Well, I suppose
there's nothing left to say. You may
leave
171:
You ARE going to stop production on
that movie, aren't you?
177:
You sure do drive a hard bargain!
Oh, all right. Consider the movie
scrapped!
185:
Do stop by again sometime. I may
yet have something else that piques
your interest!
190: Not if I can help it!
197:
Aw, crud. I totally forgot about the
ammo...
201:
True. But I suppose there's no rush,
seeing as you're free from the threat
of bounty hunters.
204:
I dunno... I'd say the ammo shortage
is a more serious issue.
208:
That reminds me. There's something
I wanted to ask you, Bulleta.
211:
Shoot. So long as it's not an overly
personal question.
214: Er, I can assure you it's not.
218:
You said you're not interested in
fame or fortune, right? But did you
end up collecting a reward for your
services on that mission?
221: I did. And a big one at that.
226:
I got my friends and the right to
gaze up at the most beautiful sky in
the world. What better reward is
there?
